				<div style="font-style:italic">Cheaper for <b>who</b> exactly?</div>
			
		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>
</div>
I'm not sure why you're disputing this point.  Single-payer health care is criticized on many fronts, but very few deny that single-payer is less expensive than our current system for everyone except the rapidly shrinking pool of individuals with largely employer-subsidized, comprehensive health benefits.  In other words, it would be more slightly expensive for you and significantly more expensive for Wandor and for me.
                  
