		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>
</div>
<br />
No, they do it for two reasons: They don't like the smell of cigarette smoke (see Daph's response below) and they want to stick it to the big corporations. If tobacco were illegal and grown by burnouts and hippies under flourescent lamps and in illicit gardens in national forests and state parks, the anti-smoking totalitarians would disappear immediately and the 420 crowd would be crowing for tobacco hemp and medical tobacco. <br />
<br />
<div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px; ">
	<div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px">Quote:</div>
	<table cellpadding="6" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
