<br />
Believe me, I can sympathize with your plight &#8212; since I gave up the smoking habit, others' cigarette smoke often makes me throat tighten up drastically, my eyes start tearing and occasionally drives me to the point where I have to get out of the room. <br />
<br />
Yet that's not enough reason to employ the legal code as a banhammer. If you want to keep it out of your home and property, great. If businesses want to ban it themselves, fine &#8212; all U.S. airlines did away with smoking on their flights long before the federal government enshrined it in the legal code, and it worked out well for them.  But let the property owners decide &#8212; you don't have to give your business to anyone who creates an environment that makes you uncomfortable. <br />
<br />
Or just ban smoking and cigarette production entirely.
                  
